<!-- 6: ERROR CLINIC -->
<!-- SECTION: Error Clinic -->
<section id="errorclinic" class="c6">
  <h2 class="sec-title"><span class="tab-num">6</span>Error Clinic</h2>
  <p>Read each sentence. Some have mistakes — fix them. <b>One sentence is already correct — do not "fix" it if it isn't broken.</b></p>
  <div class="box" style="padding:16px 20px;">
    <ol style="font-size:14.5px;">
      <li>"She wake up at 6:30." <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block'">Reveal</button><div class="reveal-content">Incorrect — "she" needs "-s": "She <b>wakes</b> up at 6:30."</div></li>
      <li>"He don't like coffee." <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block'">Reveal</button><div class="reveal-content">Incorrect — "he" needs "doesn't": "He <b>doesn't</b> like coffee."</div></li>
      <li>"My brother visits every Sunday." <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block'">Reveal</button><div class="reveal-content"><b>This sentence is already correct — no error here.</b> "Visits" correctly has "-s" for "brother" (he). Resist the urge to change anything.</div></li>
      <li>"He always is tired in the morning." <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block'">Reveal</button><div class="reveal-content">Incorrect position — with "be", the adverb goes after: "He <b>is always</b> tired in the morning."</div></li>
      <li>"Her name is Emma, and him is my daughter." <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block'">Reveal</button><div class="reveal-content">Incorrect — for a girl, we use "she": "Her name is Emma, and <b>she</b> is my daughter."</div></li>
    </ol>
  </div>
