<!-- 3: GRAMMAR -->
<!-- SECTION: Grammar Focus -->
<section id="grammar" class="c3">
  <h2 class="sec-title"><span class="tab-num">3</span>Grammar Focus</h2>

  <h3 style="color:var(--blue);">3.1 — There Is / There Are</h3>
  <p>We use <b>there is</b> (one thing) and <b>there are</b> (more than one thing) to say what exists somewhere.</p>
  <div class="table-scroll"><table class="rules">
    <tr><th>Form</th><th>Example</th></tr>
    <tr><td><b>There is</b> / <b>there's</b> + singular noun</td><td><b>There's</b> a large kitchen.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><b>There are</b> + plural noun</td><td><b>There are</b> two bedrooms.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>negative: <b>there isn't / there aren't</b></td><td><b>There isn't</b> any parking.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>question: <b>Is there...? / Are there...?</b></td><td><b>Is there</b> a bus stop nearby?</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Wh- question: <b>How many...are there?</b></td><td><b>How many</b> rooms <b>are there</b>?</td></tr>
  </table></div>

  <div class="error-box">
    <h4>⚠️ Match "Is/Are" to the Noun!</h4>
    <div class="table-scroll"><table class="rules">
      <tr><th>❌ Incorrect</th><th>✅ Correct</th></tr>
      <tr><td>There is two bedrooms.</td><td><b>There are</b> two bedrooms.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>There are a kitchen.</td><td><b>There is</b> a kitchen.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>How many rooms there are?</td><td>How many rooms <b>are there</b>?</td></tr>
    </table></div>
    <p style="margin-bottom:0;">In a Wh- question, "are there" (not "there are") — the word order flips, just like in other questions.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="ccq-box">
    <h4>🔎 Check Your Understanding</h4>
    <div class="ccq-item"><b>Do we use "there is" or "there are" for "two bedrooms"?</b> <span>There are.</span></div>
    <div class="ccq-item"><b>Do we use "there is" or "there are" for "a kitchen"?</b> <span>There is.</span></div>
    <div class="ccq-item"><b>In the question "How many rooms ___ there?", do we say "are" or "there are"?</b> <span>Are — "How many rooms are there?"</span></div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="color:var(--blue);">3.2 — Wh- Questions: A Quick Review</h3>
  <p>These question words are useful for house hunting.</p>
