  <p>Write a short restaurant conversation (<b>50–70 words</b>) between a waiter and a customer. Use at least <b>2 countable</b> and <b>2 uncountable</b> nouns, <b>some/any</b>, and both <b>like</b> and <b>would like</b>. Remember to punctuate your dialogue correctly (capital letters, question marks, commas).</p>
