<!-- 1: CONTEXT -->
<!-- SECTION: Context First: Read Before Any Rule -->
<section id="context" class="c1">
  <h2 class="sec-title"><span class="tab-num">1</span>Context First: Read Before Any Rule</h2>
  <p>Read the café's training card, then the chat about Sofia's birthday. Just try to follow the story. We look at the grammar after.</p>

  <div class="realia blogpost">
    <span class="doc-tag">Staff Training Card</span>
    <h4>Riverside Café — How to Make a Cappuccino</h4>
    <p class="byline">New staff, please read carefully!</p>
    <ol>
      <li><span class="highlight">Add</span> two spoons of coffee to the machine.</li>
      <li><span class="highlight">Pour</span> in the hot water.</li>
      <li><span class="highlight">Heat</span> the milk until it's warm.</li>
      <li><span class="highlight">Stir</span> gently, and pour the milk on top.</li>
    </ol>
    <p><span class="highlight2">Don't forget</span> to smile at every customer! <span class="highlight2">Don't add</span> sugar unless the customer asks for it. <span class="highlight2">Always wash</span> your hands before starting a shift.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="realia">
    <span class="doc-tag">Text Messages</span>
    <div class="chat">
      <div class="bubble left"><div class="name">Jack</div>How was your first shift?</div>
      <div class="bubble right"><div class="name">Pablo</div>Good, I think! I made three cappuccinos and nobody complained 😄 By the way — when's Sofia's birthday exactly?</div>
      <div class="bubble left"><div class="name">Jack</div>It's on the <span class="highlight">21st of July</span>. Should we celebrate at the café?</div>
      <div class="bubble right"><div class="name">Pablo</div>Perfect! My shift finishes at 5pm on the <span class="highlight">21st</span>, so let's meet there <span class="highlight">after that</span>.</div>
      <div class="bubble left"><div class="name">Jack</div>Great — I'll order a coffee and a slice of cake for her. What's her <span class="highlight">1st</span> choice of cake, do you know?</div>
      <div class="bubble right"><div class="name">Pablo</div>Chocolate, always! It's the <span class="highlight">3rd</span> time this month she's mentioned it.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p><em>Notice:</em> The training card uses short instructions like "Add..." and "Don't forget..." with no subject like "I" or "you" — these are called imperatives. Jack and Pablo also use numbers like "21st", "1st" and "3rd" to talk about dates and order.</p>
</section>

