<!-- 3: GRAMMAR -->
<!-- SECTION: Grammar Focus -->
<section id="grammar" class="c3">
  <h2 class="sec-title"><span class="tab-num">3</span>Grammar Focus</h2>

  <h3 style="color:var(--blue);">3.1 — Imperatives</h3>
  <p>We use imperatives to give instructions, directions, recipes, or rules. There is no subject — the sentence starts directly with the verb.</p>

  <div class="tl-diagram">
    <div class="tl-diagram-title">How to make a cappuccino: instructions in order</div>
    <svg viewBox="0 0 700 190" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <rect x="10" y="30" width="160" height="70" rx="10" fill="#5b4636"/>
      <text x="90" y="58" font-size="14" fill="#fff" font-family="Calibri" font-weight="bold" text-anchor="middle">1. Add coffee</text>
      <text x="90" y="78" font-size="11" fill="#e8ddd0" font-family="Calibri" text-anchor="middle">to the machine</text>
      <polygon points="178,60 195,54 195,66" fill="#5c5346"/>
      <rect x="200" y="30" width="160" height="70" rx="10" fill="#c17f59"/>
      <text x="280" y="58" font-size="14" fill="#fff" font-family="Calibri" font-weight="bold" text-anchor="middle">2. Pour water</text>
      <text x="280" y="78" font-size="11" fill="#f3e0d3" font-family="Calibri" text-anchor="middle">hot, not boiling</text>
      <polygon points="368,60 385,54 385,66" fill="#5c5346"/>
      <rect x="390" y="30" width="160" height="70" rx="10" fill="#4a6fa5"/>
      <text x="470" y="58" font-size="14" fill="#fff" font-family="Calibri" font-weight="bold" text-anchor="middle">3. Heat milk</text>
      <text x="470" y="78" font-size="11" fill="#dde6f0" font-family="Calibri" text-anchor="middle">until warm</text>
      <polygon points="558,60 575,54 575,66" fill="#5c5346"/>
      <rect x="580" y="30" width="115" height="70" rx="10" fill="#7d5ba6"/>
      <text x="637" y="58" font-size="14" fill="#fff" font-family="Calibri" font-weight="bold" text-anchor="middle">4. Stir</text>
      <text x="637" y="78" font-size="11" fill="#e8dff2" font-family="Calibri" text-anchor="middle">gently</text>
      <text x="350" y="135" font-size="13" fill="#2b2620" font-family="Calibri" text-anchor="middle">Every step starts with the base verb — no "I", no "you", no "-s".</text>
      <text x="350" y="158" font-size="13" fill="#8c2c2c" font-family="Calibri" font-style="italic" text-anchor="middle">Negative: Don't forget to smile. Don't add sugar unless asked.</text>
    </svg>
    <div class="tl-caption">Positive imperatives = base verb first. Negative imperatives = Don't + base verb.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="table-scroll"><table class="rules">
    <tr><th>Form</th><th>Example</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Positive: base verb first</td><td><b>Add</b> the coffee. <b>Stir</b> gently.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Negative: <b>Don't</b> + base verb</td><td><b>Don't add</b> sugar. <b>Don't forget</b> to smile.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Softer instructions</td><td><b>Please</b> wash your hands. Wash your hands, <b>please</b>.</td></tr>
  </table></div>

  <div class="error-box">
    <h4>⚠️ No Subject, No "-s"!</h4>
    <div class="table-scroll"><table class="rules">
      <tr><th>❌ Incorrect</th><th>✅ Correct</th></tr>
      <tr><td>You add the coffee.</td><td><b>Add</b> the coffee. (no subject needed)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Adds the coffee.</td><td><b>Add</b> the coffee. (no "-s" on imperatives)</td></tr>
    </table></div>
  </div>

  <div class="ccq-box">
    <h4>🔎 Check Your Understanding</h4>
    <div class="ccq-item"><b>Does an imperative sentence have a subject like "I" or "you"?</b> <span>No.</span></div>
    <div class="ccq-item"><b>How do we make an imperative negative?</b> <span>Don't + base verb.</span></div>
    <div class="ccq-item"><b>Do we add "-s" to the verb in an imperative?</b> <span>No — always the base verb.</span></div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="color:var(--blue);">3.2 — Punctuation in Your Writing</h3>
  <p>From now on, punctuation is something to check <b>every time you write</b> — not a separate rule to learn once. Here's a quick reference.</p>
  <div class="punct-grid">
    <div class="punct-card"><b>Capital letters</b> — start of every sentence, names (Pablo, Riverside Café), days and months (Monday, July)</div>
    <div class="punct-card"><b>Full stops (.)</b> — at the end of a statement or an instruction</div>
    <div class="punct-card"><b>Question marks (?)</b> — at the end of every question</div>
    <div class="punct-card"><b>Commas (,)</b> — between items in a list, and in dates ("21st of July, 2026")</div>
    <div class="punct-card"><b>Apostrophes (')</b> — in contractions (don't, it's) and possession (Sofia's birthday)</div>
    <div class="punct-card"><b>New line / list</b> — for instructions, use a new line for each step (like the training card)</div>
  </div>

  <div class="ccq-box">
    <h4>🔎 Check Your Understanding</h4>
    <div class="ccq-item"><b>Do days and months need a capital letter?</b> <span>Yes — Monday, July, etc.</span></div>
    <div class="ccq-item"><b>What punctuation mark shows "belongs to", as in "Sofia's birthday"?</b> <span>An apostrophe.</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

